def solve(a, b):
	t1, t2 = a, b
	if a.find('.') == -1:
		a += '.0'
	if b.find('.') == -1:
		b += '.0'
	x1, y1 = a.split('.')
	x2, y2 = b.split('.')
	if len(x1) > len(x2): return t1
	if len(x1) < len(x2): return t2
	for i in range(len(x1)):
		if x1[i] > x2[i]: return t1
		if x1[i] < x2[i]: return t2
	if len(y1) > len(y2): return t1
	if len(y1) < len(y2): return t2
	for i in range(len(y1)):
		if y1[i] > y2[i]: return t1
		if y1[i] < y2[i]: return t2
	return t1
print(solve(input(),input()))
